Heritage College Adelaide is an Râ€“12 school founded in 1996 by the Christadelphians who wanted to create a learning environment where the Bible was the basic foundation. The college is located at Oakden in the north-eastern suburbs of Adelaide, South Australia. It has approximately 400 students, as well as a Parents and Friends Community (PFA) and a Past Student Association (PSA).
The college is one of five Christadelphian Heritage Colleges in Australia. The others are in Perth, Lake Macquarie, Sydney and Melbourne.
